Passing values from one component to another is called as Props
Notes:
1)Parent → Child Flow
2)React follows Unidirectional Data Flow
    Data moves:
    Parent → Child
3)Props are read-only
4)Child should not modify props

1)Parent to child comp
ParentComp
import React from 'react';
import ChildComp from './ChildComp';

export default function ParentComp() {
  return (
    <>
      <p>Parent comp....</p>
      <ChildComp name="Ramani" empID="5678" />
    </>
  );
}
ChildComp:
import React from 'react';

export default function ChildComp(props) {
 
  return (
    <p>
      Child comp....{props.name} {props.empID}
    </p>
  );
}

Child comp can also be written as
a)import React from 'react';
export default function ChildComp(props) {
  const { name, empID } = props;           //type 1
 
  return (
    <p>
      Child comp....{name} {empID}
    </p>
  );
}

b)import React from 'react';

export default function ChildComp({name,empID}) {   //type2
  return (
    <p>
      Child comp....{name} {empID}
    </p>
  );
}
c) if you want to pass the number values as typeof number then use {} from parentComp, in the above 1,2 types if u console log and check the empID type will be string
ParentComp
